93
00:04:59,475 --> 00:05:01,051
Yay, Bart!

94
00:05:01,057 --> 00:05:03,820
My son's a good-for-somethin'!

95
00:05:03,825 --> 00:05:05,252
Uh, yeah, okay.

96
00:05:05,255 --> 00:05:07,131
You kids were all terrific.

97
00:05:07,137 --> 00:05:10,321
I wish I could make each
of you a Krusketeer,

98
00:05:10,326 --> 00:05:12,593
but we only have enough
money for one.

99
00:05:12,598 --> 00:05:14,123
Plus, I don't really want to.

100
00:05:14,128 --> 00:05:17,313
So after much consideration
of all your talents,

101
00:05:17,318 --> 00:05:20,013
my new Krusketeer is...

102
00:05:20,018 --> 00:05:21,353
What's your kid's name again?

103
00:05:21,355 --> 00:05:23,033
Nelson Muntz.

104
00:05:23,037 --> 00:05:24,942
Wilbur Mudd.

105
00:05:24,947 --> 00:05:25,902
That's me.

106
00:05:25,906 --> 00:05:28,011
- Here's Mudd in your eye.
- Ow!

107
00:05:29,735 --> 00:05:32,503
I can't believe I lost.

108
00:05:34,555 --> 00:05:37,371
That's not fair
Bart was great.

109
